Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 -           ]
Title: SEAT: REAR SEAT ASSEMBLY: DISASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

DISASSEMBLY

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

CAUTION:

Wear protective gloves. Sharp areas on the parts may injure your hands.

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE CENTER ARMREST HINGE COVER (for RH Side)

(a) Disengage the claw and remove the center armrest hinge cover as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

2. REMOVE REAR SEAT CENTER ARMREST ASSEMBLY (for RH Side)

(a) Remove the bolt and washer.

(b) Disengage the guide as shown in the illustration.

(c) Disengage the pin to remove the rear seat center armrest assembly as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

(d) Remove the bush as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

3. REMOVE SEAT BELT ANCHOR COVER CAP (for RH Side)

(a) Disengage the 2 claws, 2 guides and separate the rear seat shoulder belt cover with seat belt anchor cover cap.

(b) Disengage the 2 guides to remove the seat belt anchor cover cap as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

4. REMOVE REAR SEAT SHOULDER BELT COVER (for RH Side)

(a) Remove the rear seat shoulder belt cover.

5. REMOVE REAR SEATBACK LOCK CONTROL BEZEL (for RH Side)

(a) Disengage the 4 claws to remove the rear seatback lock control bezel.

6. REMOVE REAR SEATBACK BOARD SUB-ASSEMBLY RH (for RH Side)

(a) Disengage the hook.

(b) Open the 2 fasteners as shown in the illustration.

*a

Fastener

(c) Disengage the 9 claws.

(d) Disengage the 2 guides to remove the rear seatback board sub-assembly RH.

7. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER WITH PAD (for RH Side)

(a) Disengage the hook.

(b) for Center:

Remove in this Direction

(1) Disengage the 4 claws and remove the 2 rear seat headrest supports as shown in the illustration.

(c) for RH Side:

Remove in this Direction

(1) Disengage the 4 claws and remove the 2 rear seat headrest supports as shown in the illustration.

(d) Pass the rear center seat outer belt assembly through the separate type rear seatback cover with pad and remove the separate type rear seatback cover with pad from the rear seatback frame sub-assembly RH as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

8. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER (for RH Side)

(a) Using a screwdriver, disengage the 8 claws and remove the separate type rear seatback cover from the separate type rear seatback pad RH as shown in the illustration.

*a

Screwdriver

-

-

9. REMOVE REAR CENTER SEAT OUTER BELT ASSEMBLY (for RH Side)

Click here

10. REMOVE REAR SEATBACK LOCK ASSEMBLY RH (for RH Side)

(a) Remove the 2 bolts and rear seatback lock assembly RH.

11. REMOVE REAR SEATBACK LOCK CONTROL BEZEL (for LH Side)

(a) Disengage the 4 claws to remove the rear seatback lock control bezel.

12. REMOVE REAR SEATBACK BOARD SUB-ASSEMBLY LH (for LH Side)

(a) Disengage the hook.

(b) Open the 2 fasteners as shown in the illustration.

*a

Fastener

(c) Disengage the 5 claws.

(d) Disengage the 2 guides to remove the rear seatback board sub-assembly LH.

13. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER WITH PAD (for LH Side)

(a) Disengage the 4 claws and remove the 2 rear seat headrest supports as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

(b) Remove the separate type rear seatback cover with pad from the rear seatback frame sub-assembly LH as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

14. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE REAR SEATBACK COVER (for LH Side)

(a) Using a screwdriver, disengage the 8 claws and remove the separate type rear seatback cover from the separate type rear seatback pad LH as shown in the illustration.

*a

Screwdriver

-

-

15. REMOVE REAR SEATBACK LOCK ASSEMBLY LH (for LH Side)

(a) Remove the 2 bolts and rear seatback lock assembly LH.

16. REMOVE BENCH TYPE REAR SEAT CUSHION COVER

(a) Disengage the hook and 2 fasteners.

*a

Fastener

(b) Disengage the 19 hooks.

(c) Using a screwdriver, disengage the 18 claws to remove the bench type rear seat cushion cover from the rear seat cushion pad as shown in the illustration.

*a

Screwdriver
